						<b>In the first of our series "Broken Society", we have a powerful fi=
lm made by children in Hackney.</b>
<br>

<br>
They talk about living on the estates there: their experience of gang cultu=
re, gun and knife crime.=20
<br>

<br>
Earlier this year there were a series of murders of young black people in s=
outh London.
<br>

<br>
Tony Blair in April said that the spate of gun attacks was part of a "disti=
nctive black culture" rather than about poverty and deprivation.=20=20=20
<br>

<br>
Is he right? What's your experience of gangs and gun crime? Is it confined =
to one ethnic group? Let us know via our website.
<br>

<br>
Also, tell us what subjects you'd like to see us tackling as part of our "B=
roken Society" series.=20=20
<br>

<br>
To comment, and to watch tonight's report online, <a href=3D"http://www.bbc=
.co.uk/blogs/newsnight/2007/06/broken_society_hackneys_kids.html"><b>click =
here</b></a>.=20
